Section 1833(i)(2)(D) of the Social Security Act (
  42 U.S.C. 1395l(i)(2)(D)
) is amended—

subsection.text:

Section 1833(i) of the Social Security Act (
  42 U.S.C. 1395l(i)
) is amended by adding at the end the following new paragraph:

subclause.text:
the ASC
				performance score of the ambulatory surgery center under subparagraph (F);
				and

subsection.text:

Section 1833(i)(1) of the Social Security Act (
  42 U.S.C. 1395l(i)(1)
) is amended by adding at the end the following: In updating such lists for application in years beginning after the date of the enactment of this sentence, for each procedure that was requested to be included in such lists during the public comment period but which the Secretary does not propose (in the final rule updating such lists) to so include in such lists, Secretary shall cite in such final rule the specific criteria in paragraph (b) or (c) of section 416.166 of title 42, Code of Federal Regulations, based on which the procedure was excluded. If paragraph (b) of such section is cited for exclusion of a procedure, the Secretary shall identify the peer reviewed research or the evidence upon which such determination is based. The Secretary may not use or cite section 416.166(c)(7) of such title as criteria or a basis for exclusion of a procedure from such lists..
